Movie Title: Roamin' Holiday
Genres: {"/m/03k9fj": "Adventure", "/m/0hj3myq": "Children's/Family", "/m/01g6gs": "Black-and-white", "/m/02hmvc": "Short Film", "/m/01z4y": "Comedy", "/m/0hqxf": "Family Film", "/m/0hj3n26": "Family-Oriented Adventure"}
Summary: Upset at being forced to do the household chores all weekend long , Spanky, Alfalfa, Buckwheat, and Porky decide to run away from home. Taking a breather in the tiny village of Jenksville, the boys manage to cadge a meal from kindly storekeeper Mrs. Jenks. But when she finds out that the kids are runaways, she passes this information along to her husband, Constable Hi Jenks, who jovially decides to teach the boys a lesson. Pretending to arrest the four youngsters, Constable Jenks dresses them in convict stripes and forces them to work on the rockpile, figuring that after an hour or so they'll be glad to return home. But an unanticipated swarm of bees brings this little morality play to a sudden and painful conclusion for all concerned.<ref namehttp://movies.nytimes.com/movie/73841/Roamin-Holiday/overview |title2008-09-21|work=NY Times}}

